Firstly, we need to calculate the amount of area covered by one bag of chips based on condition 2 (one bag containing 72 glass chips). From condition 1, since it takes 8033625 glass chips to make up one square inch, therefore;  
Area per Bag=Total Chip Number Per Bag / Total required Glass Chip Numbers Per Square Inches=72/8033625≈0.000009 sqin.   
Next, considering our current limitation which includes having access to merely two complete bags as specified under 'current resource', hence multiplying the previous result twice results in;  
Total Coverage Area By Two Bags=(area coverage per single bag)x(number of bags)=(0.000009)*2~=0.000018sqin    
